context: <a0_0>The Ghoomar dance<a0_0/> from Jodhpur Marwar and Kalbeliya dance of <a1_0>Jaisalmer<a1_0/> have gained <b6_0>international recognition<b6_0/>. <a2_0><b7_0>Folk music<b7_0/><a2_0/> is a large part of Rajasthani culture. <b5_0>Kathputli, Bhopa, Chang, Teratali, Ghindr, Kachchhighori, and Tejaji<b5_0/> are examples of traditional Rajasthani culture. <a3_0>Folk songs<a3_0/> are commonly <b8_0>ballads<b8_0/> which relate <b9_0>heroic deeds and love stories<b9_0/>; and <a4_0>religious or devotional<a4_0/> songs known as bhajans and banis which are often accompanied by musical instruments like dholak, sitar, and sarangi are also sung.
